L2().details: Sets up the L2 contracts. Depends on `L1()` being called first.

proposeAnotherOutput().details: Helper function to propose an output.

setUp().details: Deploys the Deploy contract without including its bytecode in the bytecode      of this contract by fetching the bytecode dynamically using `vm.getCode()`.      If the Deploy bytecode is included in this contract, then it will double      the compile time and bloat all of the test contract artifacts since they      will also need to include the bytecode for the Deploy contract.      This is a hack as we are pushing solidity to the edge.

testFuzz_addLocalData_oob_reverts(uint25.details: Tests that adding local data with an out of bounds identifier reverts.

testFuzz_initialize_cannotProposeGenesis.details: Tests that the game cannot be initialized with an output root that commits to <= the configured starting      block number

testFuzz_initialize_extraDataTooLong_rev.details: Tests that the game cannot be initialized with extra data > 64 bytes long (root claim + l2 block number      concatenated)

test_addLocalDataGenesisTransition_stati.details: Tests that local data is loaded into the preimage oracle correctly in the subgame      that is disputing the transition from `GENESIS -> GENESIS + 1`

test_addLocalDataMiddle_static_succeeds(.details: Tests that local data is loaded into the preimage oracle correctly.

test_claimCredit_claimAlreadyResolved_re.details: Static unit test asserting that credit may not be drained past allowance through reentrancy.

test_constructor_wrongArgs_reverts(uint2.details: Tests that the constructor of the `FaultDisputeGame` reverts when the `_splitDepth`      parameter is greater than or equal to the `MAX_GAME_DEPTH`

test_createdAt_succeeds().details: Tests that the game's starting timestamp is set correctly.

test_extraData_succeeds().details: Tests that the game's extra data is set correctly.

test_gameData_succeeds().details: Tests that the game's data is set correctly.

test_gameType_succeeds().details: Tests that the game's type is set correctly.

test_getRequiredBond_outOfBounds_reverts.details: Tests that the bond at a depth greater than the maximum game depth reverts.

test_getRequiredBond_succeeds().details: Tests that the bond during the bisection game depths is correct.

test_initialize_correctData_succeeds().details: Tests that the game is initialized with the correct data.

test_initialize_onlyOnce_succeeds().details: Tests that the game cannot be initialized twice.

test_initialize_receivesETH_succeeds().details: Tests that the proxy receives ETH from the dispute game factory.

test_move_clockTimeExceeded_reverts().details: Tests that a move made after the clock time has exceeded reverts with the      `ClockTimeExceeded` error.

test_move_correctStatusExecRoot_succeeds.details: Tests that making a claim at the execution trace bisection root level with a valid status      byte succeeds.

test_move_defendRoot_reverts().details: Tests that an attempt to defend the root claim reverts with the `CannotDefendRootClaim` error.

test_move_duplicateClaim_reverts().details: Tests that an identical claim cannot be made twice. The duplicate claim attempt should      revert with the `ClaimAlreadyExists` error.

test_move_duplicateClaimsDifferentSubgam.details: Static unit test asserting that identical claims at the same position can be made in different subgames.

test_move_gameDepthExceeded_reverts().details: Tests that an attempt to move at the maximum game depth reverts with the      `GameDepthExceeded` error.

test_move_gameNotInProgress_reverts().details: Tests that a move while the game status is not `IN_PROGRESS` causes the call to revert      with the `GameNotInProgress` error

test_move_incorrectBondAmount_reverts().details: Static unit test asserting that a move reverts when the bonded amount is incorrect.

test_move_incorrectStatusExecRoot_revert.details: Tests that making a claim at the execution trace bisection root level with an invalid status      byte reverts with the `UnexpectedRootClaim` error.

test_move_nonExistentParent_reverts().details: Tests that an attempt to move against a claim that does not exist reverts with the      `ParentDoesNotExist` error.

test_move_simpleAttack_succeeds().details: Static unit test for the correctness of an opening attack.

test_resolve_bondPayoutsSeveralActors_su.details: Static unit test asserting that resolve pays out bonds on step, output bisection, and execution trace moves with 2 actors and a dishonest root claim.

test_resolve_bondPayouts_succeeds().details: Static unit test asserting that resolve pays out bonds on step, output bisection, and execution trace moves.

test_resolve_challengeContested_succeeds.details: Static unit test for the correctness of resolving a game with a contested challenge claim.

test_resolve_claimAlreadyResolved_revert.details: Static unit test asserting that resolve reverts when attempting to resolve a subgame multiple times

test_resolve_claimAtMaxDepthAlreadyResol.details: Static unit test asserting that resolve reverts when attempting to resolve a subgame at max depth

test_resolve_invalidStateSameAnchor_succ.details: Static unit test asserting that the anchor state does not change when the game resolves in favor of the challenger, even if the game state is newer than the anchor.

test_resolve_leftmostBondPayout_succeeds.details: Static unit test asserting that resolve pays out bonds on moves to the leftmost actor in subgames containing successful counters.

test_resolve_notInProgress_reverts().details: Static unit test asserting that resolve reverts when the game state is      not in progress.

test_resolve_outOfOrderResolution_revert.details: Static unit test asserting that resolve reverts when attempting to resolve subgames out of order

test_resolve_rootContested_succeeds().details: Static unit test for the correctness of resolving a single attack game state.

test_resolve_rootUncontestedButUnresolve.details: Static unit test asserting that resolve reverts when the absolute root      subgame has not been resolved.

test_resolve_rootUncontestedClockNotExpi.details: Static unit test for the correctness an uncontested root resolution.

test_resolve_rootUncontested_succeeds().details: Static unit test for the correctness an uncontested root resolution.

test_resolve_stepReached_succeeds().details: Static unit test for the correctness of resolving a game that reaches max game depth.

test_resolve_teamDeathmatch_succeeds().details: Static unit test for the correctness of resolving a game with multiplayer moves.

test_resolve_validNewerStateUpdatesAncho.details: Static unit test asserting that the anchor state updates when the game resolves in favor of the defender and the anchor state is older than the game state.

test_resolve_validOlderStateSameAnchor_s.details: Static unit test asserting that the anchor state does not change when the game resolves in favor of the defender but the game state is not newer than the anchor state.

test_rootClaim_succeeds().details: Tests that the game's root claim is set correctly.

test_step_duplicateStep_reverts().details: Tests that a claim cannot be stepped against twice.

test_move_clockCorrectness_succeeds().notice: Static unit test for the correctness of the chess clock incrementation.
